  "files": {
    "items": [
      {
        "id": "f_01",
        "name": "escape_plan.txt",
        "type": "txt",
        "size": "2 KB",
        "date": "Apr 18",
        "content": "If you're reading this, something went wrong.\n\nThe story is filed. Navarro has a backup copy. So does Tribune legal.\n\nVance knows I have the Monitoring Summary. He knows about Dana.\n\nBalcony key is under the desk. Don't use the front door.\n\nJ. Reyes — she's one of us. Trust her.\n\n— A"
      },
      {
        "id": "f_02",
        "name": "veridian_sources.enc",
        "type": "enc",
        "size": "48 KB",
        "date": "Apr 15",
        "content": "[ENCRYPTED — AES-256]\n\nThis file is protected. A decryption key has been provided separately to Tribune Media's legal department.\n\nDo not attempt to open on this device."
      },
      {
        "id": "f_03",
        "name": "whistleblower_agreement.pdf",
        "type": "pdf",
        "size": "156 KB",
        "date": "Apr 10",
        "content": "WHISTLEBLOWER PROTECTION AGREEMENT\n\nTribune Media Group agrees to protect the identity of source DANA PARK in perpetuity under applicable shield laws and Dodd-Frank provisions. Source has provided documentation of alleged securities violations by Veridian Group LLC.\n\nSigned: Alex Chen, Reporter | Tribune Legal Dept."
      },
      {
        "id": "f_04",
        "name": "legal_fwd.txt",
        "type": "txt",
        "size": "3 KB",
        "date": "Apr 16",
        "content": "---------- Forwarded message ----------\nDate: Apr 15, 11:42 PM\nSubject: Re: Veridian — Legal Review [CONFIDENTIAL]\n\n\"Received formal notice from Veridian Group counsel this afternoon. Claims: defamation, tortious interference. Seeking pre-publication injunction. Recommend holding publication pending 48hr counsel review. Do not inform reporter at this stage — may complicate the decision.\"\n\n[No sender. Arrived via encrypted drop.]\n\n---\nNote — A.C., Apr 16:\nNavarro knows. The 48-hour offer isn't editorial. She's stalling while legal decides whether to kill it.\n\nThe story runs regardless. That's what the backup is for."
      },
      {
        "id": "f_05",
        "name": "draft_04-17.txt",
        "type": "txt",
        "size": "1 KB",
        "date": "Apr 17",
        "content": "[UNSENT DRAFT]\n\nI keep starting this and deleting it.\n\nI don't know how to say I'm sorry for putting you here without it sounding like what it is — me needing absolution.\n\nThe agreement is real. Reyes is real. You are protected on paper.\n\nWhat I did — filing before the story was fully verified — that was for you, not for the story. I need you to know that.\n\nIf something happens to me before Tuesday: Reyes has everything. Tribune legal has everything. The story runs regardless.\n\nYou're going to be okay.\n\n— A"
      },
      {
        "id": "f_06",
        "name": "thread_backup.enc",
        "type": "enc",
        "size": "12 KB",
        "date": "Apr 19",
        "content": "[ENCRYPTED THREAD — PASSWORD REQUIRED]\n\nThis file contains a backed-up private message thread.\n\nAccess requires a passphrase. Check Photos — Alex left a note.\n\n[Hint: look at the desk photo]",
        "pinProtected": true,
        "pin": "V3R1D14N",
        "decryptedContent": "PRIVATE THREAD — A.CHEN \u2194 D.PARK (Encrypted Channel)\n\nAlex:  The plan is set. Tuesday.\nDana:  Veridian will come after you.\nAlex:  That's the point. They come after me, we document everything in real time. Someone finds the phone — they get the full picture.\nDana:  And if the wrong person finds it?\nAlex:  I've set messages to auto-send to the right people at the right time. It's handled.\nDana:  The source protection holds no matter what?\nAlex:  Tribune legal confirmed. You're protected regardless of what happens to me.\nDana:  I still think this is insane.\nAlex:  I know.\nDana:  I'm in.\nAlex:  I know that too.\n\n[THREAD END — Apr 15, 11:58 PM]"
      },
      {
        "id": "f_07",
        "name": "trash_log.txt",
        "type": "txt",
        "size": "1 KB",
        "date": "Apr 19",
        "content": "SYSTEM LOG — REMOTE FILE OPERATIONS\n\n[Apr 19 — Today]\n\n3 files deleted by remote administrator:\n\n1. veridian_board_minutes.pdf\n   Status: DELETED — Unrecoverable\n\n2. source_identity.enc\n   Status: DELETED — Partial header recoverable\n\n3. exit_plan_final.txt\n   Status: DELETED — Partial recovery possible\n\nUse the Recovery app to attempt file reconstruction."
      }
    ]
  },

